GUILT....<br><br>
I went, I served, then why do I feel guilt? I almost cry when I read of the pain and suffering of others who had it much worse than me. But for the Grace of God, there go I. More years have only brought on more guilt. Its been 26 of them now and I still &quot;often&quot; lie awake at night thinking of how I could have helped had I been &quot;in the line of fire&quot;. It only went where I was told, and did what I was told and served in the way I was told. Then why do I suffer guilt for never being shot at? <br><br>
